    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "Buying a home is the largest financial decision most Americans will ever make, and understanding your monthly mortgage payment is the first step toward making it confidently. This guide walks you through the standard amortization formula, shows you a worked example with real numbers, and points you to our free ",
        "marks": []
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-2",
        "text": "mortgage calculator",
        "marks": [
          "mark-1"
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-2",
        "text": " so you can model scenarios instantly.",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-1-h2",
    "style": "h2",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "Why Your Mortgage Payment Matters",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-2-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "Your monthly payment determines how much house you can afford, how much cash you keep for savings and emergencies, and how much interest you pay over the life of the loan. Lenders evaluate your debt-to-income ratio (DTI) — typically capping housing costs at 28% of gross monthly income — so knowing your payment before you shop prevents wasted time on homes outside your budget.",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-3-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [
      {
        "_key": "cite-1",
        "_type": "citation",
        "label": "Consumer Financial Protection Bureau",
        "url": "https://www.consumerfinance.gov/owning-a-home/"
      }
    ],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "According to the ",
        "marks": []
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-2",
        "text": "Consumer Financial Protection Bureau",
        "marks": [
          "cite-1"
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-2",
        "text": ", comparing loan estimates from multiple lenders can save you thousands over a 30-year term. A mortgage calculator lets you do that comparison in minutes.",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-4-h2",
    "style": "h2",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "The Mortgage Payment Formula",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-5-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "The standard formula for a fixed-rate mortgage is:",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-6-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "M = P × [r(1+r)^n] / [(1+r)^n − 1]",
        "marks": [
          "strong"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-7-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "Where:",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-8-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "M",
        "marks": [
          "strong"
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-1",
        "text": " = Monthly payment",
        "marks": []
      }
    ],
    "listItem": "bullet",
    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-9-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "P",
        "marks": [
          "strong"
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-1",
        "text": " = Principal (home price minus down payment)",
        "marks": []
      }
    ],
    "listItem": "bullet",
    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-10-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "r",
        "marks": [
          "strong"
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-1",
        "text": " = Monthly interest rate (annual rate ÷ 12)",
        "marks": []
      }
    ],
    "listItem": "bullet",
    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-11-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "n",
        "marks": [
          "strong"
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-1",
        "text": " = Total number of payments (years × 12)",
        "marks": []
      }
    ],
    "listItem": "bullet",
    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "_type": "block",
    "_key": "block-12-normal",
    "style": "normal",
    "markDefs": [],
    "children": [
      {
        "_type": "span",
        "_key": "span-0",
        "text": "This formula produces a level monthly payment. In the early years, most of each payment goes to interest because the outstanding balance is highest. As you pay down principal, the interest portion shrinks and the principal portion grows.",
        "marks": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
